To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Any surveillance footage, video recordings, photographs, or other visual records depicting the 10/18/25 No Kings Day Protest at or around Grant Park.  
This includes footage captured by:
Chicago Police Department cameras;
Traffic or public safety cameras operated by or accessible to the Chicago Police Department;
Mobile surveillance units;
Aerial surveillance platforms; and
Any other recording systems operated by or on behalf of the Chicago Police Department.
Any logs, indexes, inventories, retention schedules, chain-of-custody records, or metadata identifying the existence, storage, retention, transfer, or destruction of such footage.

Any records reflecting the sharing, dissemination, transfer, or provision of footage, photographs, intelligence, reports, or other information concerning the the 10/18/25 No Kings Day Protest :
The Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI);
The Department of Homeland Security;
The Illinois Sate Police;
The Crime Prevention and Information Center (CPIC);
or any other federal, state, or local law enforcement agency.

Any emails, memoranda, reports, requests, intelligence products, bulletins, or communications concerning:
the 10/18/25 No Kings Day Protest ;
Collection of information regarding participants in the 10/18/25 No Kings Day Protest ;
Requests for surveillance footage related to the 10/18/25 No Kings Day Protest  ; or
Sharing of surveillance footage or intelligence with federal agencies.
Any records sufficient to identify whether surveillance footage of the protest was retained, archived, deleted, or otherwise disposed of, and the date on which any such action occurred.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tatum Schutt

